abstract: Republican lawmakers on Wednesday proposed legislation setting a goal for the United States to plant a trillion trees by 2050 to fight global warming, a plan intended to address climate change by sucking carbon out of the air instead of by cutting emissions.
snippet: Republican lawmakers on Wednesday proposed legislation setting a goal for the United States to plant a trillion trees by 2050 to fight global warming, a plan intended to address climate change by sucking carbon out of the air instead of by cutting...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Republican lawmakers on Wednesday proposed legislation setting a goal for the United States to plant a trillion trees by 2050 to fight global warming, a plan intended to address climate change by sucking carbon out of the air instead of by cutting emissions.
headline_main: Plant a Trillion Trees: U.S. Republicans Offer Fossil Fuel-Friendly Climate Fix
headline_print_headline: Plant a Trillion Trees: U.S. Republicans Offer Fossil Fuel-Friendly Climate Fix

abstract: Bernie Sanders won New Hampshire, but the Democratic race might not be settled anytime soon.
snippet: Bernie Sanders won New Hampshire, but the Democratic race might not be settled anytime soon.
lead_paragraph: Good morning and welcome to On Politics, your guide to the day in national politics. I’m Lisa Lerer, your host, in Manchester, N.H., the morning after the New Hampshire primary.

abstract: Angela Merkel's government said on Wednesday it would restrict tenders for the procurement of sensitive weapon systems to German companies, a protectionist measure by a chancellor who has come out strongly against such barriers.
snippet: Angela Merkel's government said on Wednesday it would restrict tenders for the procurement of sensitive weapon systems to German companies, a protectionist measure by a chancellor who has come out strongly against such barriers.
lead_paragraph: BERLIN — Angela Merkel's government said on Wednesday it would restrict tenders for the procurement of sensitive weapon systems to German companies, a protectionist measure by a chancellor who has come out strongly against such barriers.
headline_main: Berlin to Limit Sensitive Military Tenders to German Firms
headline_print_headline: Berlin to Limit Sensitive Military Tenders to German Firms

abstract: Iran’s information minister apologized Wednesday for posting a photo on Twitter of what appeared to be a Halloween-type costume representing a spacesuit, in an effort to promote the idea of a manned space program for his country.
snippet: Iran’s information minister apologized Wednesday for posting a photo on Twitter of what appeared to be a Halloween-type costume representing a spacesuit, in an effort to promote the idea of a manned space program for his country.
lead_paragraph: TEHRAN, Iran — Iran’s information minister apologized Wednesday for posting a photo on Twitter of what appeared to be a Halloween-type costume representing a spacesuit, in an effort to promote the idea of a manned space program for his country.
headline_main: Iranian Minister Apologizes Over Mock Spacesuit Post
headline_print_headline: Iranian Minister Apologizes Over Mock Spacesuit Post

abstract: The Italian Senate voted by a large margin Wednesday to allow the prosecution of right-wing opposition leader Matteo Salvini for making 131 rescued migrants to remain on a coast guard vessel for days when he was Italy's interior minister.
snippet: The Italian Senate voted by a large margin Wednesday to allow the prosecution of right-wing opposition leader Matteo Salvini for making 131 rescued migrants to remain on a coast guard vessel for days when he was Italy's interior minister.
lead_paragraph: ROME — The Italian Senate voted by a large margin Wednesday to allow the prosecution of right-wing opposition leader Matteo Salvini for making 131 rescued migrants to remain on a coast guard vessel for days when he was Italy's interior minister.
headline_main: Italian Senate Votes to Lift Right-Wing Leader's Immunity
headline_print_headline: Italian Senate Votes to Lift Right-Wing Leader's Immunity

abstract: After a disappointing fifth-place finish in the Iowa caucuses, the Minnesota senator made a series of bets in the Granite State.

lead_paragraph: CONCORD, N.H. — Senator Amy Klobuchar knew she might have an opportunity in New Hampshire’s presidential primary.

abstract: Mr. Biden, 77, long the front-runner, has fallen behind two younger Democrats looking to seize the moderate mantle, and his candidacy is fragile.
snippet: Mr. Biden, 77, long the front-runner, has fallen behind two younger Democrats looking to seize the moderate mantle, and his candidacy is fragile.
lead_paragraph: MANCHESTER, N.H. — Joseph R. Biden Jr.’s fifth-place finish in the New Hampshire Democratic primary on Tuesday plunged his campaign further into peril and uncertainty, jeopardizing his fund-raising efforts and potentially upending his path to the nomination.

abstract: A tech billionaire’s PowerPoint brought the Trillion Trees climate plan to the president, a textbook case of ad hoc policymaking in the Trump era.
snippet: A tech billionaire’s PowerPoint brought the Trillion Trees climate plan to the president, a textbook case of ad hoc policymaking in the Trump era.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — People warned Marc Benioff, the billionaire chief executive of Salesforce, not to bother talking to the White House about global warming. But Mr. Benioff, a tech mogul and environmental philanthropist, felt sure he had found a climate change solution that even President Trump could love: Planting trees.
